ut.","For best results after rolling and cutting, allow pasta to dry 1-2 hours on a floured cloth.","To cook fresh pasta in your Thermomix, place 1700 g water and 1 tsp salt into mixing bowl and bring to the boil <b>10 min\/100˚C\/speed 4<b>. <b>Insert simmering basket<b> and place half the pasta (approx. 170 g) into it. Cook <b>3 min\/100˚C\/speed 4<b>. Transfer into a ThermoServer or large serving dish. Repeat with remaining pasta and serve with your favourite sauce.","<b>Green<b> <b>pasta<b>: use basic recipe with an additional 100 g flour and 70 g spinach leaves (fresh, cleaned and patted dry; or frozen, defrosted and water squeezed out). Place 300 g flour and spinach leaves into mixing bowl and mix<b> 20 sec\/speed 9<b>. Add eggs and oil and knead <b>2 min\/<b> then proceed as per recipe.","<b>Red pasta without eggs<b>: rather than 2 eggs, use 100 g tomato juice and proceed as per recipe.","To increase quantity, add 1 extra egg per additional 100 g flour. The maximum quantity at any one time is 500 g flour and 5 eggs. Increase kneading time to 3 minutes."],"basicInfo":["advanced","40m","1h","4 portions"]}